messages.content: ComfyUI-InstaSD is a collection of nodes for using with the InstaSD API builder in ComfyUI.
You can install ComfyUI-InstaSD by cloning the GitHub repository (https://github.com/WaddingtonHoldings/ComfyUI-InstaSD) into your custom_nodes directory of ComfyUI or by using the ComfyUI manager.
What should you do after installing ComfyUI-InstaSD?
After installing ComfyUI-InstaSD, you need to restart ComfyUI to load the new nodes.
Is ComfyUI-InstaSD an official part of ComfyUI?
No, ComfyUI-InstaSD is a custom node collection and not an official part of ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of ComfyUI-InstaSD nodes?
The purpose of ComfyUI-InstaSD nodes is to integrate with the InstaSD API builder in ComfyUI.
Can ComfyUI-InstaSD be used without the InstaSD API builder?
No, ComfyUI-InstaSD is designed to be used with the InstaSD API builder in ComfyUI.
Yes, ComfyUI-InstaSD is available on GitHub (https://github.com/WaddingtonHoldings/ComfyUI-InstaSD), which indicates that it is an open-source project.
